00:19:15.570 --> 00:19:17.210
be?

00:19:17.210 --> 00:19:22.710
RYAN BATEMAN: So off my head,
the one tip, the silver bullet,

00:19:22.710 --> 00:19:26.030
I would say listen
to your developers.

00:19:26.030 --> 00:19:27.920
If they feel like they're
building a bad app,

00:19:27.920 --> 00:19:29.961
odds are pretty good they
are building a bad app.

00:19:33.364 --> 00:19:35.030
Any agency, especially
in the beginning,

00:19:35.030 --> 00:19:38.880
you take the work
that you can find,

00:19:38.880 --> 00:19:41.399
and you build something
that's based on iOS.

00:19:41.399 --> 00:19:42.940
And if you listen
to your developers,

00:19:42.940 --> 00:19:45.680
they hate doing that, because
they know instinctively

00:19:45.680 --> 00:19:48.815
they're building something they
don't believe in or care about.

00:19:48.815 --> 00:19:51.190
And if you optimize for somebody
who's building something

00:19:51.190 --> 00:19:55.960
that they believe is
a quality product,

00:19:55.960 --> 00:19:57.700
then what you're
going to end up with

00:19:57.700 --> 00:20:00.085
is probably a quality product.

00:20:00.085 --> 00:20:02.376
PRADEEP NALLURI: I think the
